## Step 3 — Mock selection guide

| Dependency | Mock type | Constructor |
|-----------|-----------|-------------|
| `database.Storage` (vcp) | Interface mock | `database.NewMockStorage(t)` |
| `database.Storage` (metrics) | Interface mock | `metricsdb.NewMockStorage(t)` |
| `vsa.Provider` | Interface mock | `vsa.NewMockProvider(t)` |
| `hyperscaler.GoogleServices` | Interface mock | `hyperscaler.NewMockGoogleServices(t)` |
| `vlm.VlmWorkflowClient` | Interface mock | `vlm.NewMockVlmWorkflowClient(t)` |
| `client.Client` (Temporal) | Interface mock | `workflowenginemock.NewMockTemporalTestClient(t)` |
| `factory.OrchestratorFactory` | Interface mock | `factory.NewMockOrchestratorFactory(t)` |
| `ontaprest.StorageClient` | Interface mock | `ontaprest.NewMockStorageClient(t)` |
| `core.scheduler.Scheduler` | Interface mock | `scheduler.NewMockScheduler(t)` |
| Standalone functions (factory) | Monkey mock | `mm := newMonkeyMockAndPatch(t)` |

**When a mock doesn't exist**: Check if the interface is in `.mockery.yaml`. If not, add it and run `make generate-mocks`. For standalone functions, use the monkey mock pattern (see below).

