## Step 4 — Monkey mock usage (for standalone functions)

When testing code that calls **package-level function variables** (not interface methods):

```go
func TestCreatePool_WithMonkeyMocks(t *testing.T) {
	mm := newMonkeyMockAndPatch(t)  // patches all function vars, restores on t.Cleanup

	mm.On("utilGetLogger", mock.Anything).Return(log.NewLogger())
	mm.On("createGCPResources", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil)

	// ... test code that calls the function vars ...

	mm.AssertExpectations(t)
}
```

**Do NOT extend the monkey mock pattern to new code.** For new functions, use dependency injection (interfaces + struct fields) and generate standard mockery mocks.

